tv.com%2Findia-news%2Ffrom-police-station-rajasthan-mla-dials-civic-officials-will-break-your-heads-8879428%23publisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Inflation%20surged%20more%20than%20expected%20in%20June%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224384%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20person%20in%20a%20store%20with%20a%20cart%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F687576c6f748d8c055f59958%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223288%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20published%20new%20consumer%20price%20index%20data%20on%20Tuesday.%3Cp%3ESpencer%20Platt%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20year-over-year%20inflation%20rate%20surged%20to%202.7%25%20in%20June%20from%202.4%25%20in%20May%2C%20surpassing%20the%20forecast.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAnalysts%20expected%20that%20tariff%20effects%20would%20be%20apparent%20in%20the%20new%20report.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Federal%20Reserve%20could%20use%20the%20new%20reading%20to%20help%20decide%20whether%20to%20change%20interest%20rates%20in%20late%20July.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20year-over-year%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-inflation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einflation%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Erate%20climbed%20to%202.7%25%20in%20June%20from%202.4%25%20in%20May%2C%20surpassing%20the%202.6%25%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-may-cpi-consumer-price-index-federal-reserve-interest-rates-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Einflation%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E%20sped%20up%20for%20the%20second%20straight%20month%20and%20is%20getting%20further%20away%20from%20the%20Federal%20Reserve's%20target%20of%202%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20report%20comes%20as%20businesses%20brace%20for%20potential%20new%20tariffs.%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20once%20again%20delayed%20wide-ranging%20higher%20tariff%20rates%20that%20were%20scheduled%20to%20go%20into%20effect%20on%20July%209.%20However%2C%20Trump%20sent%20letters%20to%20countries%20like%20Japan%2C%20South%20Africa%2C%20and%20Indonesia%2C%20stating%20that%20their%20tariffs%20would%20start%20on%20August%201.%20Other%20tariffs%2C%20like%20those%20on%20steel%20and%20autos%2C%20have%20been%20in%20effect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20staggered%20implementation%20of%20tariffs%20should%20prevent%20a%20single%20month%20with%20spiking%20prices%20and%20instead%2C%20we%20can%20expect%20this%20to%20be%20the%20first%20reading%20of%20multiple%20that%20shows%20higher%2C%20but%20not%20alarmingly%20high%2C%20price%20increases%2C%26quot%3B%20Chris%20Hodge%2C%20head%20economist%20of%20the%20US%20at%20Natixis%20CIB%20Americas%2C%20said%20in%20a%20commentary%20ahead%20of%20the%20new%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlberto%20Musalem%2C%20president%20of%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20St.%20Louis%2C%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.stlouisfed.org%2Ffrom-the-president%2Fremarks%2F2025%2Fomfif-conversation-with-president-musalem%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elast%20week%3C%2Fa%3E%20it's%20too%20soon%20to%20know%20whether%20tariffs%20will%20have%20a%20temporary%20or%20persistent%20effect%20on%20inflation.%20New%20York%20Fed's%20survey%20of%20consumer%20expectations%20showed%20median%20household%20expectations%20for%20inflation%20one%20year%20ahead%20slowed%20from%203.6%25%20in%20March%20and%20April%20to%203.2%25%20in%20May%20and%203%25%20in%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20Federal%20Open%20Market%20Committee%20meeting%20is%20in%20two%20weeks%2C%20in%20which%20members%20will%20discuss%20what%20to%20do%20with%20interest%20rates%20based%20on%20inflation%2C%20the%20job%20market%2C%20and%20other%20data.%20Before%20the%20new%20inflation%20report%2C%20CME%20FedWatch%20showed%2C%20based%20on%20interest%20rate%20traders%2C%20that%20there's%20an%20overwhelming%20chance%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20will%20hold%20interest%20rates%20steady.%20Data%20published%20at%20the%20start%20of%20July%20showed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjune-jobs-report-unemployment-rate-employment-federal-reserve-interest-rates-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eunemployment%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20still%20fairly%20low%20and%20even%20fell%20from%204.2%25%20to%204.1%25%20in%20June.%20However%2C%20labor%20force%20participation%20also%20dropped%2C%20wage%20growth%20cooled%2C%20and%20long-term%20unemployment%20rose.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20a%20developing%20story.%20Please%20check%20back%20for%20updates.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-june-cpi-consumer-price-index-federal-reserve-interest-rates-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1752582774000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F687576c6f748d8c055f59958%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-june-cpi-consumer-price-index-federal-reserve-interest-rates-2025-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Inflation%20is%20speeding%20up%20after%20a%20period%20of%20cooling%20down%20earlier%20this%20year.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Madison%20Hoff)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A26%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-june-cpi-consumer-price-index-federal-reserve-interest-rates-2025-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US%20Operated%20Iraqi%20Oil%20Field%20On%20Fire%20After%20Drone%20Strike%20During%20Attacks%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22An%20oil%20field%20in%20Iraq%20's%20Dohuk%20province%20was%20set%20ablaze%20Tuesday%20after%20being%20struck%20by%20a%20drone.%22%2C%22published%22%3A1752582721000